The paper presents a methodology for analyzing and controlling the energy consumption of a commercial soccer stadium, which involves integrating existing instrumentation into a Cyber-Physical System. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. Additionally, the paper focuses on energy efficiency, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) sub-category. The paper also develops and tests different control strategies, which involves machine learning techniques such as Deep Belief Networks, suggesting that it could belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the transferability of the methodology to other stadiums and building types, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) sub-category.
